posts.title: A Note From A Long Timer
posts.content:
I joined r/The_Donald in 2015 a month after it was formed.

Stayed for the memes, then stayed for the message, then stayed for the news, then stayed to celebrate, research, dig, etc… I got to watch one of the biggest websites on earth be forced to take unfair action because we were too powerful. Everyone who has been a part of this community has been able to take a stab at the establishment by rallying behind one man. We know he won in 2020, but… this victory hits different.

Let’s not forget that Trump had an AmA with us.

Let’s not forget the feds were infiltrating us here, trying all sorts of psyops on us, but we meme’d them into submission.

Let’s not forget that Trump’s staff lurks here, so keep up with the insights.

T_D was the primary place catalyst the internet that originated Trump’s online movement and got him elected. Nothing could convince me otherwise.

I know the last four years have been legitimately shitty for our American culture, economy, and freedoms. But, it’s always darkest before the Don.

MAGA forever. I love you guys.
